## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] nice(10) applied at startup (POSIX - works on Linux + macOS)
- [ ] I/O priority: Linux uses ioprio_set(IDLE), macOS uses setiopolicy_np(THROTTLE)
- [ ] Non-supported platforms log info and continue (no crash)
- [ ] Memory limit enforced via setrlimit (with macOS caveat logged)
- [ ] Thread pool bounded to min(4, cpus/2)
- [ ] ONNX runtime threads also bounded
- [ ] Memory monitor uses /proc/meminfo (Linux) or sysctl+vm_stat (macOS)
- [ ] Memory pressure triggers model eviction (LRU or largest-first)
- [ ] Configuration file parsed with sensible defaults
- [ ] Env var overrides config file values
- [ ] All settings logged at daemon startup for diagnostics
