Evaluate nomic-embed-text-v1.5, which offers long context + MRL in a small package.

## Model Details
- Source: Nomic AI (December 2024, still competitive in 2025+)
- Parameters: 137M
- Dimensions: 768 (MRL-enabled: 64, 128, 256, 384, 512, 768)
- Context: 8192 tokens (longest context in our benchmark!)
- MTEB Retrieval: 55+ (very strong for size)
- Special: Matryoshka, long context, binary quantization support

## Why This Model Is Important
nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is unique in our benchmark because:
1. 8192 token context: Can embed full Grok conversations without truncation
2. Flexible MRL: Supports many truncation points (64 to 768)
3. Binary quantization: Can reduce storage by 32x with minimal quality loss
4. Strong baseline: Despite being from late 2024, still very competitive

## Architecture
```rust
pub struct NomicEmbedder {
    session: ort::Session,
    tokenizer: tokenizers::Tokenizer,
    native_dims: usize,          // 768
    target_dims: Option<usize>,  // MRL truncation
    max_length: usize,           // 8192
    task_prefix: String,         // "search_query: " or "search_document: "
    name: String,
}

impl Embedder for NomicEmbedder {
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        // nomic uses task-specific prefixes:
        // For queries: "search_query: {query}"
        // For documents: "search_document: {doc}"
        // For clustering: "clustering: {text}"
        // For classification: "classification: {text}"
        let prefixed: Vec<String> = texts.iter()
            .map(|t| format!("{}{}", self.task_prefix, t))
            .collect();

        let encodings = self.tokenizer.encode_batch(
            prefixed.iter().map(|s| s.as_str()).collect::<Vec<_>>(), true
        )?;

        // Note: 8192 context means potentially large inputs
        // Must handle memory carefully for long documents
        let max_len = encodings.iter().map(|e| e.len()).max().unwrap_or(0)
            .min(self.max_length);

        let input_ids = build_padded_tensor(&encodings, max_len, 0);
        let attention_mask = build_attention_mask(&encodings, max_len);

        let outputs = self.session.run(ort::inputs![
            "input_ids" => input_ids,
            "attention_mask" => attention_mask,
        ]?)?;

        // Mean pool with attention mask
        let hidden = outputs[0].extract_tensor::<f32>()?;
        let mut results = Vec::with_capacity(texts.len());
        for i in 0..texts.len() {
            let mut pooled = mean_pool_with_mask(
                &hidden, i, max_len, self.native_dims, &attention_mask
            );
            if let Some(target) = self.target_dims {
                pooled.truncate(target);
            }
            l2_normalize(&mut pooled);
            results.push(pooled);
        }
        Ok(results)
    }

    fn dimensions(&self) -> usize { self.target_dims.unwrap_or(self.native_dims) }
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn supports_mrl(&self) -> bool { true }
}
